result.name: Kam Kee Cafe

reviews.text: Love having a quick meal here after my run. For $57 you'll get a nice hot bowl of macaroni (or rice noodles) in soup with sliced beef, two fried eggs (done your way) with well buttered toast and a nice icy cold milk tea. Great value for money. Friendly staff and comfortable seating. Didn't take long for food to come. Definitely recommend this cafe.

Price was not expensive in the shopping area, so shared table was a common practice.  Food and drink was acceptable with a few old style drink available.  Enough staff here, service was good and fast.

A must visit establishment. Quick service, great food, friendly staff (as much as can be expected when one is in Hong Kong) and clean surrounds. I went for the sliced beef broth with scrambled eggs and brioche toast alongside and iced milk tea which all came to just under £5. An absolute winner and would definitely go back.

The cheesy rice was not too bad, but the service provided by the man who took the order was fantastic. He gave some recommendations and even followed up if everything was good. Very attentive and courteous - I was impressed. Good service makes a difference!

Tried black bean sauce stir fried noodles,  tomato pork cutlets and rice, coffee and milk tea. Price was very reasonable and the English menu definitely helped with ordering. The staff there also spoke English which was handy. Service is almost non-existent however that seems to be the norm everywhere in Hong Kong.
